  <prompt>
    Document the typed config schema model (FR-16 / Invariant 5) in `docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md`.
    Cover: what GetConfigSchema() returns, the endpoint URL + payload shape, who the consumer is
    (PlaybookBuilder canvas, Wave 8 task 083), the forward-compat strategy for new field types, and
    a worked example. Audience: future authors of new executors + canvas maintainers.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Technical writer + architect. Concise sections, worked examples, no over-explanation. Mirror the
    existing AI-ARCHITECTURE.md style (sectioned, code-snippet-heavy, cross-referenced to ADRs).
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new section in `docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md` (placement: alongside the existing
    node-executor pattern documentation) covering:
    1. WHAT — the GetConfigSchema() method on INodeExecutor and the ExecutorConfigSchema/ConfigFieldDescriptor records
    2. WHY — Invariant 5 / FR-16 motivation: PlaybookBuilder canvas drives typed forms from data
    3. ENDPOINT — `GET /api/ai/playbook-builder/executor-config-schemas` URL + auth + payload example
    4. WORKED EXAMPLE — one rich schema (AiCompletionNodeExecutor) + one placeholder
    5. AUTHOR GUIDANCE — when adding a new executor, declare its schema; how to choose field types; how to handle conditional fields
    6. FORWARD-COMPAT — what happens when canvas encounters an unknown field `type` (warning state per FR-27 pattern)
    7. CROSS-REFERENCE — link to FR-16, ADR-010, ADR-013, `.claude/patterns/ai/node-executor-authoring.md`
  </goal>

  <inputs>
