    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Worked example: AiCompletion rich schema">
      Inline a 10-15 line JSON snippet showing what AiCompletionNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema() returns when serialized. Pull the exact field names from task 032's implementation if shipped; otherwise from task 030 design doc.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Worked example: placeholder">
      One-line JSON: `{ "fields": {} }`. Note that 28 of 33 executors use this shape in v1 and will be enriched in follow-on waves.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Cross-references + author guidance">
      Close with bullet points: when adding a new executor, declare a schema; pick field types from {string, number, boolean, object, array}; use `required: true` only for fields the executor's Validate() actually requires; use `default` to communicate the executor's default behavior to the canvas.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify acceptance">
      Read the section as a future executor author. Could they implement a new schema from this section alone, without reading source? If not, tighten.
    </step>
